468
01:12:38,978 --> 01:12:40,854
Hello.

469
01:12:43,357 --> 01:12:48,821
We've already received an offer
for your services. $25,000 a year.

470
01:12:48,988 --> 01:12:53,492
- Who from?
- Manufacturers Intelligence Group.

471
01:12:55,995 --> 01:12:58,372
Never heard of them.

472
01:12:59,415 --> 01:13:03,711
They work out of
the Hammond building in Atlanta.

473
01:13:04,795 --> 01:13:10,801
- What do they want me to do?
- Work in their security programme.

474
01:13:11,468 --> 01:13:14,680
- Sounds good to me.
- Good.

475
01:13:17,933 --> 01:13:21,103
Just one more thing.

476
01:13:21,645 --> 01:13:23,605
What's that?

477
01:13:30,404 --> 01:13:32,740
Who are you?

478
01:13:38,829 --> 01:13:43,500
- Who am I?
- You're not Richard Paley.

479
01:13:43,667 --> 01:13:46,754
Your service records don't check.

480
01:13:48,005 --> 01:13:49,631
They don't?

481
01:13:49,798 --> 01:13:55,304
There was a Richard Paley
in the 1 st Air Cavalry, but he's dead.

482
01:13:57,681 --> 01:14:02,269
- Gee, I'm sorry to hear that.
- So were we.

483
01:14:03,645 --> 01:14:06,607
Who are you?

484
01:14:08,108 --> 01:14:11,528
I don't have to tell you. You're not a cop.

485
01:14:12,780 --> 01:14:17,784
I was getting attached to you.
I wouldn't step outside that door.

486
01:14:27,336 --> 01:14:29,671
We simply have to know.

487
01:14:31,882 --> 01:14:34,843
All right.

488
01:14:35,552 --> 01:14:37,888
My name's Richard Partun.

489
01:14:38,055 --> 01:14:41,725
Why did you want us to think
you were Richard Paley?

490
01:14:41,892 --> 01:14:47,648
I needed a job. I got into a little difficulty
in El Monte a couple of months ago.

491
01:14:47,814 --> 01:14:51,902
What kind of difficulty? It's important.

492
01:14:52,069 --> 01:14:57,658
I was drinking in this bar and...
I used to drink a lot.

493
01:14:59,910 --> 01:15:05,123
Next thing I know, I'm running around
a laundromat with no clothes on.

494
01:15:05,290 --> 01:15:09,169
Some old lady
claimed I was trying to...

495
01:15:11,004 --> 01:15:15,133
- You know, molest her.
- Were you?

496
01:15:15,300 --> 01:15:20,138
I don't know. I don't remember
what I was doing there, nothing.

497
01:15:20,305 --> 01:15:27,479
All I know is that they arrested me for...
indecent exposure.

498
01:15:29,064 --> 01:15:35,737
A thing like that follows you around.
Try to get a job, you're a sex offender.

499
01:15:35,904 --> 01:15:39,616
- I'm no sex offender.
- No, I'm sure you're not.

500
01:15:39,783 --> 01:15:44,997
I think they put something in my beer
that made me take off my clothes.

501
01:15:47,082 --> 01:15:52,671
If that's all there is to it, we'll check it out
with the El Monte police.

502
01:15:53,755 --> 01:15:57,843
It'll be no problem... Richard.

503
01:15:59,469 --> 01:16:02,973
I've tried to be a friend to you, haven't I?

504
01:16:04,725 --> 01:16:10,272
At Parallax, I've found that people
who have had real trouble in their lives,

505
01:16:10,439 --> 01:16:13,775
so-called antisocial people,

506
01:16:13,942 --> 01:16:20,490
if I can earn their loyalty, I can give them
a sense of their own worth.

507
01:16:20,657 --> 01:16:24,703
That's very rewarding, believe me.

508
01:16:24,870 --> 01:16:30,167
I honestly think, with your nature,
you're more reliable for security work

509
01:16:30,333 --> 01:16:36,006
than any semi-retired ex-FBI agent
they can come up with.

510
01:16:36,173 --> 01:16:40,927
In a risk situation,
I believe you'll go right down the line.

511
01:16:42,012 --> 01:16:45,098
That's something money can't buy.

512
01:16:47,726 --> 01:16:50,604
You're invaluable, Richard.

513
01:16:54,441 --> 01:17:00,489
<i>- ... ex-FBI agent they can come up with. 
- Oh, come on, Frady.</i>

514
01:17:00,655 --> 01:17:06,661
<i>... I believe you'll go right down the line. 
That's something money can't buy. </i>

515
01:17:09,956 --> 01:17:12,542
<i>You're invaluable, Richard. </i>

516
01:17:25,055 --> 01:17:27,474
Come in, Stanley.

517
01:17:28,225 --> 01:17:30,310
There you are.

518
01:17:31,895 --> 01:17:33,980
You're new, aren't you? Thanks.

519
01:18:47,762 --> 01:18:52,058
It must have been 5.30.
That's when I come to clean the office.

520
01:18:52,225 --> 01:18:56,187
- There he was.
- All the signs of a massive coronary.

521
01:18:56,354 --> 01:19:00,734
- D'you know if he had a heart condition?
- I don't know.

522
01:19:05,947 --> 01:19:10,910
Trusting man. He didn't even
lock the drawer he kept his money in.

523
01:19:17,709 --> 01:19:20,336
I'm very pleased with you.

524
01:19:23,423 --> 01:19:29,304
Tomorrow, you'll meet with the other
member of your team, Ben Harkins.

525
01:19:29,471 --> 01:19:31,806
He'll have your assignment.

526
01:19:33,308 --> 01:19:37,520
I just...
What name am I supposed to use?

527
01:19:37,687 --> 01:19:41,941
Richard Partun.
Don't worry, he knows all about you.

528
01:19:43,068 --> 01:19:45,153
Good.

529
01:20:41,835 --> 01:20:44,128
Good afternoon. 803, isn't it?

530
01:20:44,295 --> 01:20:48,132
The guy that just checked in,
is his name Ben?

531
01:20:48,299 --> 01:20:50,927
I can't remember his last name.

532
01:20:51,094 --> 01:20:57,016
Harkins. It's Mr Ben Harkins.
816, right down the hall from you.

533
01:21:13,700 --> 01:21:17,787
Ben Harkins, please. Ben Harkins.

534
01:21:23,751 --> 01:21:26,337
Ben?

535
01:21:26,504 --> 01:21:29,424
I got a message for you from Jack.

536
01:21:29,591 --> 01:21:33,011
Don't unpack.
There's been a change in plans.

537
01:21:33,177 --> 01:21:35,430
How much money you got left?

538
01:21:35,597 --> 01:21:40,310
<i>- I don't know, maybe $700.
- There'll be another $200 at the desk.</i>

539
01:21:40,476 --> 01:21:45,231
Go back to the airport and
take the 510 American to Honolulu.

540
01:21:45,398 --> 01:21:49,152
<i>- Honolulu? 
- Not bad, uh?</i>

541
01:21:49,319 --> 01:21:53,448
When you get to Honolulu,
take the first flight to Maui.

542
01:21:53,614 --> 01:22:00,163
When you get there, rent a jeep and
drive to a hotel called the Hana Ranch.

543
01:22:00,330 --> 01:22:03,833
<i>- Yeah, Hana Ranch. Got it?
- Right. </i>

544
01:22:18,848 --> 01:22:23,311
- Is Jack Younger here?
- Mr Younger isn't here.

545
01:22:29,400 --> 01:22:34,697
Richard Partun was here. The guy
he sent me to meet didn't show up.

546
01:25:30,706 --> 01:25:32,625
People, let's work now.

547
01:25:32,792 --> 01:25:37,254
Would you please
check your cards for sequence?

548
01:25:41,926 --> 01:25:45,805
Check your cards carefully
for sequence.

549
01:25:49,058 --> 01:25:53,813
Work smoothly
and it'll be a clean, clear picture.

550
01:25:53,979 --> 01:25:59,193
I'm gonna give you a warning,
"One, two, three" and a command, "Pull".

551
01:26:01,320 --> 01:26:06,492
Get your concentration here.
Make a good, clean, sharp picture.

552
01:26:06,659 --> 01:26:08,035
Here we go.

553
01:26:14,834 --> 01:26:18,629
All right. And one, two, three, pull!

554
01:26:23,300 --> 01:26:26,387
One, two, three, turn!

555
01:28:16,538 --> 01:28:18,707
One, two, three, lift!

556
01:28:20,250 --> 01:28:23,128
Applause, applause. Here he comes.

557
01:28:23,295 --> 01:28:26,090
Here's the man himself, Mr Hammond.

558
01:28:32,721 --> 01:28:35,182
- Quite a surprise.
- Nice to see you.

559
01:28:35,349 --> 01:28:38,352
This is Pat Fairfield,
Student Body President.

560
01:28:38,519 --> 01:28:41,855
Marilyn Puttnam,
Student Federation President.

561
01:28:42,022 --> 01:28:44,316
The youth is rallying, sir.

562
01:28:44,483 --> 01:28:47,861
We're at that point
where you'll be coming in.

563
01:28:48,028 --> 01:28:51,740
- If you would make your entrance.
- What I'm here for.

564
01:28:51,907 --> 01:28:55,869
- Where do I enter?
- Round the table, up the stair.

565
01:28:56,036 --> 01:28:58,831
- Right to the speaker stand.
- OK.

566
01:29:00,374 --> 01:29:06,213
Card people, we have a tape of the
address Mr Hammond's going to deliver.

567
01:29:06,380 --> 01:29:09,675
We're gonna run that
so you can learn your cues.

568
01:29:09,842 --> 01:29:12,177
I'll be giving cues for applause.

569
01:29:12,344 --> 01:29:16,181
When he comes in,
greet him for everybody here.

570
01:29:16,348 --> 01:29:21,854
Here he comes, making his entrance.
Let's hear it! Come on!

571
01:29:26,942 --> 01:29:31,488
That's the man we're working for,
the man people are coming to see.

572
01:29:31,655 --> 01:29:34,575
This is gonna be on television.

573
01:29:48,839 --> 01:29:54,303
Wanna thank you kids for being here,
and the band. See you tonight.

574
01:29:58,348 --> 01:30:02,394
<i>Thank you. 
I am proud to be here tonight. </i>

575
01:30:02,561 --> 01:30:07,024
<i>I can think of no occasion
that has given me more pleasure. </i>

576
01:30:11,528 --> 01:30:14,740
<i>We all ache for the chance
to be proud again. </i>

577
01:30:14,907 --> 01:30:19,453
<i>I promise you I will not stop, 
I will not falter, </i>

578
01:30:19,620 --> 01:30:22,581
<i>till that march
has reached its destination. </i>

579
01:30:22,748 --> 01:30:25,292
<i>Until, like Moses, I've returned to you</i>

580
01:30:25,459 --> 01:30:29,296
<i>the promised land of liberty
our forefathers created. </i>

581
01:30:36,345 --> 01:30:40,933
<i>I cannot take the honours
you bestow on me as a personal tribute. </i>

582
01:30:41,099 --> 01:30:47,481
<i>You are here to honour me
not as a man but as a representative... </i>

583
01:30:47,648 --> 01:30:52,027
...they're all talking about Jack Nicklaus,
Palmer.

584
01:30:52,194 --> 01:30:54,988
<i>Our cause must become the country's. </i>

585
01:32:51,146 --> 01:32:52,814
<i>I am proud... </i>

586
01:32:58,945 --> 01:33:02,782
<i>Our cause must become the country's. </i>

587
01:33:02,949 --> 01:33:09,456
<i>My life has been blessed with success, 
but that is not why you are here. </i>

588
01:33:09,623 --> 01:33:12,417
<i>My life has been blessed with... </i>

589
01:33:44,699 --> 01:33:47,702
There he is! There he is!

590
01:37:21,958 --> 01:37:24,585
I see him!

591
01:38:15,011 --> 01:38:18,723
Ladies and gentlemen,
you've been invited here

592
01:38:18,890 --> 01:38:24,395
for the announcement of the inquiry
into the death of George Hammond.

593
01:38:24,562 --> 01:38:29,859
A complete transcript of the investigation
is in preparation.

594
01:38:30,026 --> 01:38:34,614
This committee has spent
six months of investigation,

595
01:38:34,781 --> 01:38:38,075
followed by 11 weeks of hearings.

596
01:38:39,702 --> 01:38:41,954
After careful deliberation,

597
01:38:42,121 --> 01:38:48,419
it has concluded that George Hammond
was assassinated by Joseph Frady.

598
01:38:48,586 --> 01:38:50,838
An overwhelming body of evidence

599
01:38:51,005 --> 01:38:55,801
has revealed that Frady was obsessed
with the Carroll assassination.

600
01:38:55,968 --> 01:38:59,138
And in his confused and distorted mind

601
01:38:59,305 --> 01:39:04,977
seems to have imagined that Hammond
was responsible for the senator's death.

602
01:39:05,144 --> 01:39:10,900
He was equally convinced
that Hammond was plotting to kill him.

603
01:39:11,067 --> 01:39:16,822
It is for those reasons
that Frady assassinated him.

604
01:39:16,989 --> 01:39:22,578
Although I'm certain that it will do nothing
to discourage the conspiracy pedlars,

605
01:39:22,745 --> 01:39:26,165
there is no evidence of a conspiracy

606
01:39:26,332 --> 01:39:30,211
in the assassination
of George Hammond.

607
01:39:30,378 --> 01:39:32,421
Those are our findings.

608
01:39:32,588 --> 01:39:38,302
The evidence will be available
to you as soon as possible. Thank you.

609
01:39:38,469 --> 01:39:41,097
This is an announcement, gentlemen.

610
01:39:41,264 --> 01:39:44,308
There will be no questions.

